<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12189h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12189h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12189h"> 189(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ in 4 beds <font face="wake">H</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">294: Instead <font color="green">[in thirteenth-century Wales]</font> we find groups of kinsmen who hold jointly, according to carefully laid down rules, a definite area of land. <font color="green">[Footnote 1: &ldquo;It is to be known that there is a certain <i>progenies</i> of free tenants in this commote which is called the progenies of Rand Vaghan ap Asser.&rdquo; Then are given the lands they held, &ldquo;and they held all the above <mark>in four beds</mark>.&rdquo; Here <i>progenies</i> equals the Irish <i>sliocht</i>: bed, in the Latin text <i>lectum</i>, is the Welsh <i>gwely</i>.]</font> <small> W.F. Butler, &ldquo;Irish Land Tenures&rdquo; <a name="IRLT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#IRLT"><cite title="source">Studies</cite></a> (June 1924) 294</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
